	heliospheric imagers (HI) (science data) from 8 years of observations by five in situ observing spacecraft. We use 
	the self‐similar expansion model for CME fronts assuming 60$\,^{\circ}$ longitudinal width, constant speed, and constant 
	propagation direction. With these assumptions we find that 23\%--35\% of all CMEs that were predicted to hit a 
